我是你的合伙律师  亚当
I thought I was your co-counsel, Adam.

66
00:03:54,810 --> 00:03:55,690
如果你手里有王牌
If you're holding a trump card,

67
00:03:55,690 --> 00:03:57,590
难道不该和我分享一下吗
don't you think maybe you should share it with me?

68
00:03:57,660 --> 00:03:59,220
这场庭审会很棒的
It's going to be a good trial.

69
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:01,220
我们进去吧
Come on, let's get inside.

70
00:04:12,420 --> 00:04:13,650
你没必要这样做
You don't have to do this.

71
00:04:13,650 --> 00:04:14,770
艾沃说有必要
Ivo says we do.

72
00:04:14,770 --> 00:04:16,310
你的朋友们对他的人来说是个威胁
Your friends are a danger to his men.

73
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:17,880
快去  别惊动他们
Go. Quick and quiet.

74
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,130
斯莱德  莎朵  快跑
Slade! Shado! Run!

75
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,490
里面没人
There's no one here.

76
00:04:36,850 --> 00:04:38,680
他们肯定转移了
They must have moved on from their position.

77
00:04:39,080 --> 00:04:41,080
炸药放好了  这是引爆器
Chargers are placed. Here's the detonator.

78
00:04:41,080 --> 00:04:43,610
确保他们无"家"可归
Make sure they have no place to return to.

79
00:04:44,790 --> 00:04:45,710
去吧
Go.

80
00:04:46,210 --> 00:04:47,050
你
And you.

81
00:04:48,580 --> 00:04:50,330
现在你要带我们去墓地
Now you're going to take us to the graves.

82
00:04:50,650 --> 00:04:52,340
走吧  拉他起来
Let's go. Get him up.

83
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:55,530
动身
Let's get clear.

84
00:05:01,130 --> 00:05:02,550
你找到引爆器了吗
Did you find the detonator?

85
00:05:02,550 --> 00:05:03,380
找到了
Yes.

86
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:07,990
我们真走运
We were lucky.

87
00:05:08,610 --> 00:05:11,250
是我走运  你很厉害
I was lucky. You were good.

88
00:05:12,130 --> 00:05:13,080
不管怎样
Either way...

89
00:05:13,990 --> 00:05:15,090
奥利弗都在他们手上
they have Oliver.

90
00:05:15,980 --> 00:05:17,050
我去找他
I'm going after him.

91
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:18,960
我陪你去
Not alone.

92
00:05:20,310 --> 00:05:21,730
你都没法走路
You can barely walk.

93
00:05:23,110 --> 00:05:25,100
所以我更不能待在这里
All the more reason not to stay here.

94
00:05:25,660 --> 00:05:27,710
不能再给他们一次把我炸飞的机会
Give them another chance at blowing me up.

95
00:05:35,060 --> 00:05:35,930
你俩没事吧
Are you two ok?

96
00:05:35,930 --> 00:05:37,140
我该问你这个问题
I should be asking you that question.

97
00:05:37,140 --> 00:05:38,180
我没事
I'll be fine.

98
00:05:38,190 --> 00:05:39,720
你看上去像得了流感
You look like you have the flu.

99
00:05:39,990 --> 00:05:40,790
如果真是那样  我不该
If that's true, I shouldn't

100
00:05:40,790 --> 00:05:42,460
浪费时间接种疫苗的
have wasted my time getting vaccinated.

101
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:44,920
狄格尔  不管是怎么回事  回家去吧
Diggle, whatever it is, just go home.

102
00:05:45,530 --> 00:05:47,300
奥利弗  我能处理好的  好吗
Oliver, listen, I can take care of things. All right?

103
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:49,200
不  我们没事的
No, we'll be fine, all right?

104
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,200
去休息吧  别逼我叫警察
Go rest. And don't make me call a cop.

105
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,900
这里就有几个
There are a few of them around here.

106
00:06:20,050 --> 00:06:22,800
我被迫参与了一项事业
I have been complicit in an undertaking

107
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:25,010
它有一个恐怖的目的
with one horrible purpose--

108
00:06:25,490 --> 00:06:28,370
摧毁贫民区以及里面每一个人
to destroy the glades and everyone in it.

109
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:32,360
奏效了  贫民区被毁
And it worked. The Glades were destroyed.

110
00:06:32,360 --> 00:06:34,350
哀横遍野  人们流离失所
Homes and lives were lost.

111
00:06:34,350 --> 00:06:36,530
都是因为她的行为
All because of her actions.

112
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,460
确实  她想清楚之后做了悔改
True, she had second thoughts;

113
00:06:38,460 --> 00:06:42,100
自责促使她发表这份声明
remorse which compelled her to deliver this statement.

114
00:06:42,100 --> 00:06:44,580
但我想替那天逝去的503条生命
But on behalf of the 503 lives

115
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:46,180
在这里说一句话
that were extinguished that day,

116
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:49,740
莫伊拉·奎恩  你的自责太迟了
I say, Moira Queen, your remorse comes too late.

117
00:06:50,200 --> 00:06:52,110
在过去的五年里
For the last five years,

118
00:06:52,790 --> 00:06:54,180
我和我家人的生命
under the threat for my life

119
00:06:54,180 --> 00:06:56,090
受到了威胁
and the lives of my family...

120
00:06:57,130 --> 00:06:59,260
为什么这些威胁没有让她沉默
Why wouldn't those threats silence her?

121
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:02,430
为什么莫伊拉·奎恩没有被吓倒
Why wouldn't Moira Queen be terrified?

122
00:07:02,780 --> 00:07:05,230
马尔科姆·梅林杀了她的第一任丈夫
Malcolm Merlyn killed her first husband,

123
00:07:05,230 --> 00:07:06,550
绑架了她的第二任丈夫
abducted her second.

124
00:07:06,550 --> 00:07:08,610
她为什么不担心自己的性命
Why wouldn't she be in fear for her life?

125
00:07:08,940 --> 00:07:10,690
不担心自己儿女的性命
For the lives of her children?

126
00:07:11,920 --> 00:07:12,970
你们会怎么做
What would you do?

127
00:07:13,480 --> 00:07:15,560
如果你们的子女
If it were your children in the crosshairs

128
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:17,250
被一个疯子控制
of a mad man's rage?

129
00:07:21,410 --> 00:07:23,690
星级实验室的粒子加速器
They say the Star lab's particle accelerator

130
00:07:23,690 --> 00:07:26,050
会如期开启
will be turned on right on schedule.

131
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,900
其他新闻  我们刚刚收到消息
In other news, we have just received word

132
00:07:27,900 --> 00:07:30,730
莫伊拉·奎恩庭审中的正反两方
that both sides have now completed their opening statements

133
00:07:30,730 --> 00:07:32,540
都已经完成了开庭陈词
in the Moira Queen trial.

134
00:07:32,610 --> 00:07:34,770
别理解错了  但你看起来很恶心
Don't take this the wrong way, but you look disgusting.

135
00:07:34,770 --> 00:07:36,670
好吧  我感觉不太好  费利西蒂
Yeah, well, I don't feel great, Felicity.

136
00:07:37,590 --> 00:07:39,360
